                                        <h3 style="color:black">5. Milam Glacier Trek :</h3>
                                        
                                        <p>The Himalayan region of Kumaon is a storehouse of natural beauty beyond belief, protected from the onslaught of the outside world, the Himalayan ecology remains well conserved here, making the region a great retreat for the lovers of nature. The trek to the Milam Glacier is amongst the best of treks in this region, taking you through some of the remotest areas with breathtaking panorama. The Milam Glacier, approximately 700 kms. from Delhi lies in Johar Valley of Pithoragarh district, the eastern most part of Uttarakhand. The Valley is locally known as Milam Valley. Milam Village is the last village of the valley which is also one of the highest villages in Himalayan range. Till the year 1962 the People of Johar Valley used to do trading with Tibet through the passes of Unta Dhura and Kungribhingri la. This trek all the way across the Goriganga river takes you to the snout in Milam Glacier through the dense and beautiful forests of Rhododendrons, Oak, Pine, Cedar and Bhojpatra. Splendid Waterfalls and beautiful Alpine Meadows makes you spellbound. On the way you pass through the eastern part of Nanda devi Sanctuary and have fantabulous views of Nanda devi east (7430 mtrs.), Nanda devi(7820 mtrs.), Hardeol(7161 metres) and Trishuli(7070 mtrs.). One can have gigantic view of Nanda devi east and Nanda devi peaks from Bilju. The Milam Glacier trek is among the best trek Kumaun himalaya range through remote areas with breathtaking panorama. The Milam Glacier, situated on the south-facing slope of the Himalayan range, It originates from the slopes of Kohli and Trishul peaks. It is the source of the Milam River and a tributary of the Pindar River. On the way of Milam Glacier trek the route is also divert for Nandadevi base. Places on the way of this tour are Nanda Devi East Base, Gauri Ganga, Lilam, Railkot, Mapa, Martoli, Munsyari. Milam Glacier Trek gives an opportunity to explore and experience the beauty of Indian Himalaya. Trekking journey begins from Munsyari to Milam. The trek involves moderate walks using good treks to cross through rugged terrains, quaint villages and picturesque streams. PanchaChuli range captivates the scenic trek on ascending to the Lilam ridge.</p>
                                        
                                        
